Definition: the act of damaging the appearance or surface of something
Example: the defacement of an Italian mosaic during the Turkish invasion; he objected to the dam's massive disfigurement of the landscape
Synonyms: verb, contact, deface, disfigurement, disfigure, disfiguration, mutilation, damage, the, act, of, damaging, appearance, or, surface, something, an, Italian, mosaic, during, Turkish, invasion, he, objected, to, dam, s, massive, landscape
Category: noun.act
